last_episode_to_air.name: Down to the Wire
last_episode_to_air.overview: Wrexham AFC's poor away form casts doubt on their chances for promotion, and as the end of the season nears, Rob McElhenney and Ryan Reynolds face some very tough decisions.

name: Welcome to Wrexham
overview: Documentary series tracking the dreams and worries of Wrexham, a working-class town in North Wales, UK, as two Hollywood stars (Rob McElhenney and Ryan Reynolds) take ownership of the town’s historic yet struggling football club.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: In Season 3, with the team taking their place in the EFL, the cameras have unprecedented access on the pitch, bringing viewers inside the locker room and alongside the players, while the action unfolds in some of the biggest matches Wrexham AFC has ever played.

episodes.name: Dream
episodes.overview: Hollywood stars Ryan Reynolds and Rob McElhenney attempt a takeover of the world’s third oldest professional football (a.k.a. soccer) club, located in Wrexham, a working class town in northern Wales in the United Kingdom.

episodes.name: Reality
episodes.overview: Wrexham Football Club attempts to qualify for the playoffs as their new owners try to (very quickly) learn the ins and outs of a game and an industry they know nothing about.

episodes.name: Rebuilding
episodes.overview: With just weeks before the season begins, Rob McElhenney and Ryan Reynolds find themselves having to convince star football players and executives to take a chance on Wrexham.

episodes.name: Home Opener
episodes.overview: The first Wrexham home opener of the new era arrives, whether Rob McElhenney and Ryan Reynolds are ready for it or not.

episodes.name: Fearless
episodes.overview: Ryan Reynolds and Rob McElhenney land an important partnership as the Wrexham goalies - and fans - face some tough contests.

episodes.name: Hamilton!
episodes.overview: Ryan Reynolds and Rob McElhenney try to fulfill one of their biggest promises to Wrexham as a previous owner’s dark shadow still lingers.

episodes.name: Wide World of Wales
episodes.overview: In this "very special episode", Ryan Reynolds and Rob McElhenney take us through on a tour of Wales - and TV show formats.

episodes.name: Away We Go
episodes.overview: Wrexham Chairmen Ryan Reynolds and Rob McElhenney make a surprise appearance at an away game to watch Wrexham play in person for the very first time.

episodes.name: Welcome Home
episodes.overview: After a year of cheering from afar due to Covid, Co-Chairmen Ryan Reynolds and Rob McElhenney finally get to visit Wrexham and spend time with their team and the town.

episodes.name: Hooligans
episodes.overview: Unfortunate occurrences at the first home game attended by the Co-Chairmen lead to a police investigation and raise the ugly specter of football Hooliganism.

episodes.name: Sack the Gaffer
episodes.overview: Fans grumble about Wrexham's lackluster performance and aim their ire at manager Phil Parkinson. Ryan Reynolds and Rob McElhenney debate his future with the club.

episodes.name: Wins and Losses
episodes.overview: Wrexham AFC begin to play up to their potential while off the field challenges put match play in perspective.

episodes.name: Worst Team in the League
episodes.overview: Roster changes threaten Wrexham's momentum as they prepare to face the worst team in the league.

episodes.name: A Hollywood Distraction
episodes.overview: Ryan Reynolds surprises the team with a visit as Wrexham prepares for the biggest match of the season against Stockport County, their rivals for promotion.

episodes.name: Daggers
episodes.overview: With one match left to play in the regular season, Wrexham has a chance to win the league and promotion.

episodes.name: Hello Wembley
episodes.overview: Hollywood stars and Wrexham residents descend on London for the Red Dragons' big match at legendary Wembley Stadium.

episodes.name: Wromance
episodes.overview: An inside look at the unusual beginnings and dynamics of Ryan Reynolds and Rob McElhenney's football friendship.

episodes.name: Do or Die
episodes.overview: For the first time in 14 years, Wrexham has a chance to be promoted out of the National League. Can they do it?

episodes.name: Welcome Back to Wrexham
episodes.overview: A new football season begins as the town, the team and owners Ryan Reynolds and Rob McElhenney prepare to welcome King Charles III.

guest_stars.name: King Charles III of the United Kingdom
guest_stars.original_name: King Charles III of the United Kingdom

episodes.name: The Quiet Zone
episodes.overview: Wrexham striker Paul Mullin tackles challenges on and off the pitch as we meet Wrexham superfan Millie Tipping.

episodes.name: Nott Yet
episodes.overview: Wrexham are playing well but their hopes for promotion are under threat thanks to the amazing play of a surging rival – Notts County.

episodes.name: Shaun's Vacation
episodes.overview: Some self-inflicted chaos unfolds in Wrexham thanks to Co-Chairmen Ryan Reynolds and Rob McElhenney, much to the frustration of Executive Director Humphrey Ker.

episodes.name: First Losers
episodes.overview: After a second place finish last season and with Notts County challenging for first place, Wrexham AFC focuses on building a winning mentality.

episodes.name: Ballers
episodes.overview: The most dominant football team in Wales takes the pitch as they race toward promotion while juggling their day jobs.

episodes.name: Giant Killers
episodes.overview: The FA Cup provides Wrexham a chance to live up to its storied past and to take on teams playing many leagues above them.

episodes.name: The Grind
episodes.overview: Injuries, the weather and a brutal schedule test Wrexham AFC as the team enters do or die time.

episodes.name: Glove Triangle
episodes.overview: The return of Rob Lainton complicates the goalie situation while Co-Chairmen Rob McElhenney and Ryan Reynolds make a difficult roster decision.

episodes.name: Gresford
episodes.overview: The darkest day in Wrexham history looms over the team and town as they try to shift to a winning mentality.

episodes.name: Yn Codi
episodes.overview: The Wrexham Women's Team battle for promotion and try to set a Welsh attendance record at the Racecourse.

episodes.name: Hand of Foz
episodes.overview: Wrexham AFC and Notts County clash at the Racecourse in the biggest match in the history of the National League.

episodes.name: Family Business
episodes.overview: Family is everything for the members of Wrexham AFC and we meet the fathers, mothers, daughters and sons behind some key people.

episodes.name: Worst Case Scenario
episodes.overview: With promotion still up in the air, Co-Chairmen Rob McElhenney and Ryan Reynolds bring in friends and sponsors to help raise the Club's profile.

episodes.name: Up the Town?
episodes.overview: Wrexham faces either promotion or the dreaded playoffs.

episodes.name: Welcome to the EFL
episodes.overview: Wrexham AFC play a series of summer "friendlies" in America and have a less than friendly return to the English Football League.

episodes.name: Goals
episodes.overview: New players take the pitch and a shocking departure surprises Wrexham as the team tries to find its footing.

episodes.name: Notts Again
episodes.overview: The Wrexham Women's Team adapt to life in the top Welsh league as the men prepare to face Notts County, their fiercest rivals from the National League.

episodes.name: Risky Business
episodes.overview: The Birthday Prank War between Co-Chairmen Rob McElhenney and Ryan Reynolds escalates as Wrexham is reminded of the fragility of the city's rebound on and off the field.

episodes.name: Temporary
episodes.overview: 99-year-old Wrexham fan Arthur Massey reflects on his life as a supporter as his 100th birthday approaches and the Club continues to struggle with the new Kop football stand.

episodes.name: Far Away, So Close
episodes.overview: Wrexham's global impact can be felt as far away as Patagonia and The Gambia but the team can't seem to win away from the Racecourse.

episodes.name: Proper Trouble
episodes.overview: With a rise in yellow cards and continuing poor form away from home, Wrexham AFC risk being relegated to the playoffs while the women's side prepare to tackle new challenges.

episodes.name: Down to the Wire
episodes.overview: Wrexham AFC's poor away form casts doubt on their chances for promotion, and as the end of the season nears, Rob McElhenney and Ryan Reynolds face some very tough decisions.
